onies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":34,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":45,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":47,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Gyles Alwyn of Pitminster was born in 1524, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom. He married Johanne Brixton in 1550, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom. He died on 17 August 1572, in Somerset, England, at the age of 48, and was buried in Pitminster, Somerset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1524–17 August 1572":"1524–17. august 1572","1529–1572":"1529–1572","1556–1629":"1556–1629","1524–1572":"1524–1572","1550":"1550","4 May 1567":"4. mai 1567","1572":"1572","1571":"1571","about 1529":"umbes 1529","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1524":"1524","1556":"1556","17 August 1572":"17. august 1572","1629":"1629","1529":"1529","1549":"1549","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Pitminster, Somerset, England":"Pitminster, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1524–17 August 1572":"1524–17. elokuuta 1572